<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-395-562  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 395 562.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Design  April 16 1990 v29 n8 p8(1).andM;ne</JOURNAL><TITLE>EIA raps export restrictions. (Electronics Industries Association)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Shapiro, Syd.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Electronics Industries Association (EIA) is calling for awholesale reexamination of the US export commodity jurisdictionsystem.andP;  EIA representatives, claiming the viability of the USeconomy is at stake, are urging Congress to relax US export rulesfor products with dual military and commercial uses.andP;  The EIAclaims the problems stem from the State Department's growingtendency to control products that were previously under thejurisdiction of the Commerce Department.andP;  EIA VP and senior legaladvisor Joseph R. Creighton feels the Department of Defense, whenunhappy with the way the Department of Commerce is controlling aproduct, will persuade the State Department to add it to theMunitions List.andP;  Items on the list cannot be sold outside the USand Canada without special authorization.andP;  The EIA feels too manynonmilitary items are on the list and, instead of strengtheningour national security, the restrictions are undermining theeconomy.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Trade DeficitEconomicsExportMilitaryElectronic Industries AssociationUnited States. Congress.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>